Custom version of ReloadOptions mutator, made with ServerPerks support!

Now it will show in your ESC-Menu (Like in the screenshot)

[h1][b][u]Credits[/u][/b][/h1]

- 10⁻³ m³
- ScaryGhost for code reference
- Me

[h1][b][u]Whitelist status[/u][/b][/h1]

- NO (?) Test and check yourself.

[h1][b][u]Notes[/u][/b][/h1]

- 100% Support for 1080p & 720p resolutions
- 100% Support for ServerPerks
- No matter how many tabs you have in ESC-Menu, it will always show there. e.g. ServerTools tab & Server Achievments tab, now you will also see ReloadOptions tab

[h1][b][u]Number Of Files[/u][/b][/h1]

- 2 (For the server)
- 1 (Config, for the clients)

[h1][b][u]Sample Config (CLIENTS ONLY)[/u][/b][/h1]

[code]
[ReloadOptionsSP.RldOptInteraction]
bAllowInterrupt=True
bDisableAuto=False
bNoAmmoMsg=True
bInterruptMsg=True
bNeedReloadMsg=False
InterruptAliases=Fire
InterruptAliases=AltFire
InterruptAliases=ThrowNade
InterruptAliases=ThrowGrenade
InterruptAliases=GetWeapon
InterruptAliases=SwitchWeapon
InterruptAliases=SwitchToLastWeapon
[/code]

This configuration is AUTOMATICALLY generated when you change your settings from the ESC-Menu. You don't have to create it manually.

[h1][b][u]File Names[/u][/b][/h1]

- \System\ReloadOptionsSP.u
- \System\ReloadOptionsSP.ucl
- \System\ReloadOptionsSP_Config.ini

[h1][b][u]Usage[/u][/b][/h1]

1- Subscribe or download manually (Recommended)
2- Launch the game and wait to see 'Completed'
3- Restart the game and you can see the mutators in your list

[h1][b][u]Class Names[/u][/b][/h1]

- Mut: ReloadOptionsSP.ReloadOptionsSP

[h1][b][u]Manual Download Links (Recommended)[/u][/b][/h1]

- Github: https://github.com/Bleeding-Action-Man/ReloadOptions_Custom/releases/tag/v1.0